Differential Gene Expression Analysis of hornet castes

Emeline Favreau

2023-01-31

Copyright 2023 Emeline Favreau, University College London.

This is a short version of code for our Scientific Reports manuscript. For the longer version, check it on Github.

Objectives of analysis

Brains of workers (5 pools), gynes (5 pools) and 1 queen (no pool) of Vespa crabro have been sequenced for RNA. The behavioural differences between castes are expected to be measured using brain RNAseq as proxy. Which genes are significantly differentially expressed between castes?

Analysis steps:

  • Obtaining data
  • Formatting data
  • Aim 1: Run DESeq2 on all samples

Aim 1: Run DESeq2 on all samples

I first check potential sample outliers looking at normalised read counts (with a heatmap, a sample-to-sample dendogram, a PCA) and a barplot of DEG value ranges.
